#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:46
msgid ""
"Accelerator that opens the Quick Entry capture modal. Phase 6 binds this; "
"declared here from Phase 3 so the value persists across versions. GTK "
"accelerator syntax — e.g. \"<Control>n\"."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:55
msgid "Use the high-legibility font (Atkinson Hyperlegible)"
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:56
msgid ""
"When enabled, swaps the UI font from Inter to Atkinson Hyperlegible — a "
"typeface designed by the Braille Institute for low-vision readers, with high "
"inter-letter distinguish- ability. Bundled (SIL OFL 1.1) so the toggle works "
"with no system fonts required. Phase 8c."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:67
msgid "Org-mode vault directory"
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:68
msgid ""
"Absolute path to a directory holding `.org` files that Atrium projects its "
"data into (Phase 16, spec §7.3). Empty string means \"no vault configured\" "
"— Atrium runs DB-only, which is a valid configuration. Convention is `$HOME/"
"Tasks/`. The Settings → Org Vault → Choose folder UI to manage this lands in "
"Phase 19.5; the `--vault PATH` CLI flag overrides for this session."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:81
msgid "System notifications master switch"
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:82
msgid ""
"When enabled, Atrium fires `gio::Notification` for time-based reminders "
"(`task.reminder_at`). When disabled, the reminder service stays running but "
"suppresses every notification. Phase 19.5 (v0.20.0)."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:92
msgid "Theme override"
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:93
msgid ""
"One of \"auto\" (follow system Adwaita), \"light\", or \"dark\". v0.20.0 — "
"Phase 19.5 preferences foundation. The Adwaita style manager already auto-"
"tracks system scheme; this key exists for users who want to pin one "
"regardless of system setting."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:104
msgid "Weekly automatic database backup"
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.gschema.xml:105
msgid ""
"When enabled, Atrium writes a timestamped database snapshot to "
"`$XDG_DATA_HOME/atrium/backups/` at launch if the newest existing snapshot "
"is more than seven days old, keeping the newest ten. Off by default; manual "
"\"Back up now\" works regardless. v0.32.0 — Phase 19.5."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.metainfo.xml.in:8
msgid "Local-first GTD task manager with a native GNOME design"
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.metainfo.xml.in:11
msgid ""
"Atrium is a native GNOME task manager that fuses Things 3 clarity with "
"OmniFocus depth via a mode switch over a shared local-first data store. Pick "
"Simple Mode for what-am-I-doing-right-now; switch to Builder Mode when you "
"want full GTD review, deferral, sequential projects, and forecast. Same "
"data, two surfaces, no migration."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.virinvictus.atrium.metainfo.xml.in:18
msgid ""
"Storage is one SQLite file at $XDG_DATA_HOME/atrium/atrium.db, written by a "
"single dedicated worker thread so the UI never blocks on I/O. The schema is "
"the OmniFocus superset on day one: Simple Mode hides the Builder fields, it "
"doesn't lack them. An optional Org-mode vault mirrors the database as round-"
"trippable .org files so your data stays portable to Emacs, Logseq, or a pile "
"of files in a git repo."
msgstr ""

